# Why: Three call sites in upstream code hardcode `INTERNAL_CLAIM_ID.FREE` (or
#      the lowercase shorthand `internalClaims.free`) when creating a new
#      organisation. For BizRethink self-host these need to point at the new
#      BIZRETHINK tier (introduced in overlay 001) so every org gets full
#      feature flags by default. The three paths are:
#
#        1. createPersonalOrganisation in
#           packages/lib/server-only/organisation/create-organisation.ts
#           — fires automatically when a new user signs up.
#        2. createOrganisationRoute in
#           packages/trpc/server/organisation-router/create-organisation.ts
#           — fires when a user creates an org via the UI.
#        3. createAdminOrganisationRoute in
#           packages/trpc/server/admin-router/create-admin-organisation.ts
#           — fires when an admin creates an org via the admin panel.
#
#      Patching only one path leaves the other two on FREE; we need all three.
#
# Why-not-additive: Each of the three call sites is in upstream code that we
#      neither own nor can wrap. There's no DI hook or env-var indirection for
#      "which claim does a new org get." Each is a one-line substitution; the
#      admin route also needs an import to expose INTERNAL_CLAIM_ID.
#
# Upstream-merge-fragility: LOW. Each change is a single token swap on a
#      well-named line. Even if upstream refactors a callsite, re-anchoring is
#      mechanical (look for `internalClaims[INTERNAL_CLAIM_ID.FREE]` near
#      `createOrganisation({` and substitute BIZRETHINK).
#
# Status: APPLIED 2026-04-29.

